 GAUTENG coronavirus positive cases continue to rise as the province has the highest numbers in the country. As of Sunday, Gauteng had 1148 people that had contracted the virus, with 551 having recovered. The breakdown by district of the cases in the province is as follows. The City of Joburg has 690, the City of Ekurhuleni has 233 positive cases, while the City of Tshwane has 122, Sedibeng 11, West Rand 39 and 53 cases have not been allocated. The province to date has reported six people that have died due to the virus.   GLOBAL CASES LOCAL CASES  STATISTICS PER COUNTRY 